other_tests.findings: Tachycardic, S1/S2, no murmurs, gallops, or rubs; crackles left base, distant breath sounds; + CVA tenderness L>R.

Mild bibasal atelectasis; pancreas diffusely enlarged and hypoenhancing; small to moderate amount of peripancreatic fluid; kidneys normal with a 34 x 33 x 31 mm round lesion in the right interpolar region thought to be a non-specific finding.
Negative for Neisseria gonorrhoeae by APTIMA COMBO 2 Assay.
